    Alpha-gal Sensitization in a U.S. Screening Population is Not Associated with Decreased Meat Intake or Gastrointestinal Symptoms.
 Elevated alpha-gal IgE antibodies were common and not associated with reduced mammalian meat intake, abdominal pain or diarrhea. Seropositivity did not predict symptomatic alpha-gal sensitization in this general screening population. Other host factors likely contribute to phenotypic expression of alpha-gal syndrome.
